  "name": "Intoxicating Petal",
  "system": {
    "description": {
      "value": "<p><strong>Associated Skill: </strong>Knowledge (nature)</p><p><strong>Associated Weapon Groups: </strong>Bows, flails, hammers, and thrown</p><p><strong>Accessing the Discipline</strong>: An advanced discipline, Intoxicating Petal builds on the lessons imparted by related schools of combat. So long as an initiator has access to a discipline that shares at least two associated weapons with Intoxicating Petal, they may trade one of their disciplines for access to this one. If they do, they gain Knowledge (nature) as a class skill.</p><p><strong>@UUID[Compendium.pf1-pow.rules.JournalEntry.uGLFs7wz4gPuyz1V.JournalEntryPage.m4RnTvYPjZeW0Wcy]{Sprout}</strong>: Intoxicating Petal maneuvers interact with and inflict the sprout condition; causing supernatural plantlife to sprout and grow upon the targets of their maneuvers. Maneuvers that use this condition are marked with the [sprout] tag. The exact nature of the plantlife that grows is determined by the initiator, most commonly determined when they first gain this discipline. Examples include flowers, vines, roots, leaves, or fungus.</p><p><strong>Special</strong>: Maneuvers from this discipline are universally supernatural in nature, due to how they manipulate plant constructs and vital energy.</p>",
      "instructions": ""
    },
